  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.7.3-stable\r\nGit Commit: 4bb3c89d44e372e6a9ab85a8be0c9345265c763a\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.9\r\nOperating System: linux (Ubuntu 16.04)\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.9\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nSync in reasonable amount of time\r\nOn an Amazon `m5.4xlarge` instance\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nStill syncing after about 6 hours...\r\n```\r\n> eth.syncing\r\n{\r\n  currentBlock: 5071336,\r\n  highestBlock: 5071572,\r\n  knownStates: 60220021,\r\n  pulledStates: 60199988,\r\n  startingBlock: 0\r\n}\r\n>\r\n```\r\n```\r\n> eth.blockNumber\r\n0\r\n> \r\n```\r\n\r\n60 million `pulledStates`, really?\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nDownload latest version of geth\r\n`geth --syncmode \"fast\" console 2>>~/geth.log`\r\n\r\n",
